        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix Telegram forum-topic subagent completion delivery",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Simplifies native sub-agent completion handoff: child agents no longer receive the `message` tool and their result is the latest visible assistant text from the child session.\n- Removes manual sub-agent control surfaces from `/subagents`, the model-facing `subagents` tool, and UI `/steer`/`/redirect`; these are visibility/status only now.\n- Keeps parent/requester delivery policy intact: `message_tool_only` routes still require the parent handoff to use `message` or intentionally stay silent, and generated media must be delivered by the message tool before fallback is skipped.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Native sub-agents report back to the previous/parent agent through the last visible assistant turn, without requiring child-side `message` tool usage or `/subagents` manual control actions.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout and Blacksmith Testbox OpenClaw checkout for the changed gate.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n- `pnpm test ui/src/ui/chat/slash-commands.node.test.ts ui/src/ui/chat/slash-command-executor.node.test.ts src/agents/subagent-announce-output.test.ts src/agents/subagent-announce-delivery.test.ts src/agents/subagent-announce.format.e2e.test.ts`\n- `pnpm prompt:snapshots:check`\n- `pnpm protocol:check`\n- `/Users/steipete/Projects/agent-scripts/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main`\n- `pnpm check:changed`\n\nEvidence after fix: Terminal output from the local and Testbox OpenClaw runs showed `Prompt snapshots are current (7 files).`, `protocol:check` completed with no diff, focused UI tests passed 49 tests, focused agent/gateway/e2e tests passed 147 tests, autoreview reported no accepted/actionable findings, and Blacksmith Testbox `tbx_01ksadq74a21pxffw2zg473qpt` exited 0 for `pnpm check:changed`.\n\nObserved result after fix: Sub-agent result extraction ignores tool/toolResult output, preserves earlier visible assistant text across trailing empty/tool-call turns, suppresses explicit silent markers, no longer exposes send/steer/spawn/kill sub-agent control actions, and generated-media completions on message-tool-only routes require media evidence from the message tool before direct fallback is skipped.\n\nWhat was not tested: Live Telegram delivery. Maintainer proof override is appropriate because the behavioral surface is covered by focused unit/e2e tests plus the full changed gate.\n",
